definitions.definition: To manage an area of responsibility in a way which is inept , incompetent , or dishonest .
examples: She mismanaged my finances and left me bankrupt.

definitions.definition: To behave, in a management capacity, in a manner which is inept, incompetent, or dishonest.
examples: The fundamental reason why the company failed is that the CEO and other top managers simply mismanaged .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To manage an area of responsibility in a way which is inept , incompetent , or dishonest .
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To behave, in a management capacity, in a manner which is inept, incompetent, or dishonest.
